### NOTES

# 1. AUTHENTICATION:
#    - All endpoints except webhook require JWT token
#    - Get token from login endpoint: POST /users/login
#    - Include as: Authorization: Bearer <token>

# 2. VERIFICATION FLOW:
#    - Create session → Get URL → User uploads docs → Webhook fires → Status updated

# 3. DOCUMENT TYPES:
#    - Driving License (UK): Required to become a driver
#    - Passport: Accepted for identity verification, but not sufficient for driver role

# 4. WEBHOOK:
#    - Only Stripe should call the webhook endpoint
#    - Requires valid Stripe signature
#    - See README.md for complete webhook setup guide

# 5. RATE LIMITS:
#    - No explicit rate limits on these endpoints
#    - Stripe has their own rate limits on verification sessions

# 6. TESTING:
#    - Use Stripe test mode in development
#    - Test webhooks locally using Stripe CLI
#    - See README.md for local webhook testing setup

# 7. RETURN URL:
#    - Must be a valid URL
#    - Should be your frontend page where user lands after verification
#    - Can include query parameters for tracking

# 8. SESSION EXPIRATION:
#    - Stripe verification sessions expire after 30 days
#    - If expired, user must create a new session

# 9. SECURITY:
#    - Webhook signature verification is critical
#    - Never disable signature verification in production
#    - Store STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET securely in .env

# 10. COMPLIANCE:
#     - Stripe Identity is PCI compliant
#     - Documents are encrypted at rest
#     - No document images are stored on our servers